<DOCNO> XIE19990815.0003 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-14 18:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Health Situation Worsening in Iraq, Says Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Health Minister Omid
Medhat Mubarak said on Saturday that surveys made recently by the
U.N. Children and Education Fund (UNICEF) show that the health
situation in Iraq is worsening due to the U.N. sanctions.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak told a press conference that the worsening health
situation is due to the widespread malnutrition, infectious
diseases, severe shortages of medicine and medical appliances.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that the UNICEF surveys, made in
coordination with the Iraqi Health Ministry, showed that the
mortality rates of newly born infants and children under the age
of five amounted to 18 percent and 13 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The worsening environment situation, the continuation of the
U.S.-British bombardment of civilian facilities, power failure and
the severe lack of spare parts for medical appliances also lead
to the worsening health situation, said the minister.
</P>
<P>
He said that many hospitals, especially children hospitals,
need to be reconstructed, adding that 30,000 hospital beds needs
to be changed.
</P>
<P>
The minister expressed hope that Iraq would soon get the
medical appliances and equipment to put an end to the worsening
of the health situation.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak refuted the U.S. allegations that the Iraqi government
should be responsible for the worsening health situation of the
country, saying that those allegations are nonsense and can not
be believed by any fair-minded people.
</P>
<P>
He said that two teams sent by World Health Organization (WHO)
to Iraq to verify the U.S. allegations that Iraq stores medicine
and medical appliances in its warehouses refuted the
U.S. allegation as untrue.
</P>
<P>
The minister accused the U.S. and Britain of putting pressure
on some companies to cancel their health contracts signed with
Iraq, and suspending Iraq's contracts concluded with foreign
countries.
</P>
<P>
He called for the total lifting of the U.N. sanctions imposed
on the Iraqi people for more than nine years, saying that to allow
Iraq to import freely food, medicine and medical appliances is
the only solution to the end of the suffering of the Iraqi
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
