<DOCNO> XIE19990815.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-14 17:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Total Saudi Aid to Kosovo up to 49 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia has so far
extended a total of 49 million U.S. dollars in relief aid to
Kosovo, a Saudi official said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Chairman of the Saudi Red Crescent Society Saleh
Al-Tuwaijri said that Riyadh began to supply the Kosovo refugees
with relief aid after the U.S.-led North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) forces launched air strikes against
Yugoslavia on March 24.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi aid included foods and medical equipment, the Saudi
Press Agency quoted Al-Tuwaijri as saying.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the air raids which led to hundreds of
thousands of Kosovo Albanians fleeing to neighboring countries,
an air corridor was established, through which some daily Saudi
flights were flown from the Saudi capital of Riyadh to the Tirana
Airport in Albania, which harbored a large number of Kosovo
refugees.
</P>
<P>
Some of the Saudi relief supplies were also shipped to Albania
from the kingdom's western port city of Jeddah.
</P>
<P>
After NATO called off the war against Yugoslavia, the Saudi
government also contributed in rebuilding the war-torn
Kosovo. 
