<HEADLINE> Ethiopian State Bank Soon to Be Privatized: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's state-owned
Construction and Business Bank (CBB), formerly known as the
Housing and Saving Bank, is to be privatized soon, informed
sources said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In order to complete the transfer of the 60 million birr (7.5
million U. S. dollars) capital bank before the end of 1999, a
foreign consultancy agency is currently conducting assets
evaluation and assessing the 11 modalities proposed for the CBB's
privatization, the sources disclosed.
</P>
<P>
CBB, which turned into its present form in 1995, has a
20-branch network and has provided an outstanding loans of 8.7
million birr (1.1 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian Finance Minister Sufian Ahmed said Saturday that
government- owned enterprises, which are intended to be
privatized, should examine their accounts prior to the beginning
of the privatization process.
</P>
<P>
According to Ethiopian Privatization Agency General Manager
Beshah Azmite, activities are underway to convert some of the
state-owned enterprises into share companies.
</P>
<P>
The government has designed a mechanism that world enable
workers remain with their enterprises after the privatization
takes place, he said.
</P>
<P>
Some 123 government-owned enterprises in the country will be
privatized, the agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
