<HEADLINE> Johnston Retains WBC Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Stevie Johnston retained his
WBC lightweight title by winning over Angel Manfredy with an
unanimous decision on Saturday night in Mashantucket, the United
States.
</P>
<P>
Judges Terry Smith and Tommy Kaczmarek scored the fight 116-112,
while judge Bob Logist marked it 118-111.
</P>
<P>
Johnston, who successfully defended the title for the second
straight time, had lost the WBC lightweight crown in June 1998,
but defeated Bazan in a rematch in February.
</P>
<P>
In another fight, former IBF junior lightweight champion Arturo
Gatti made a successful debut as a junior welterweight, scoring a
first-round knockout of Reyes Munoz.
</P>
<P>
Gatti (30-4) sent Munoz to the canvas with one second left in
the first round. The win was the first for Gatti since October 4,
1997, when he stopped Gabriel Ruelas in the fifth round.  
</P>
