<HEADLINE> China Ready for First PECC Trade, Investment Expo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Invitations have been sent out
and preparations are in full swing for the first Trade and
Investment Exposition of the Pacific Economic Cooperation Council
(PECC), which will be hosted September 14-18 in this north China
port city.
</P>
<P>
This was announced today after relevant officials ended a
meeting on the exposition, to be held in the Tianjin Economic and
Technological Development Zone.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce
Jing Shuping, Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
Shi Guangsheng and Tianjin Mayor Li Shenglin were among those
attending today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
According to sources at the preparatory committee, over 260
enterprises from 20 countries and regions will attend the
exposition, which is hosted jointly by the PECC, the Chinese
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, and the
Tianjin Municipal People's Government.
</P>
<P>
Half of the 440 booths have been reserved for overseas
companies, and some 12,000 business people are expected to attend
the exposition, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The exposition, with the theme "Environment and Housing in the
21st Century", will display new technologies and materials
connected with environmental protection and house building.
</P>
<P>
The PECC is a non-governmental organization of scholars and
experts from some 20 countries and regions, whose aim is to seek
economic cooperation and development in the Pacific region.
</P>
</TEXT>
