<HEADLINE> Lebanese Civilian Wounded in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A Lebanese civilian was wounded
Sunday during Israel's shellings on villages in south Lebanon, the
Voice of the People radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Ali Mohammed Mustafa, 65, was injured when shells fired by
Israeli troops fell on the village of Touline in the central
sector of the Israeli occupied border zone in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The attack raised to 130 the number of Lebanese civilians
wounded in south Lebanon since the start of this year. Another 18
were killed over the same period.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon
in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from
Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by the
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has been fighting to
oust Israeli occupation troops out of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
