<HEADLINE> 166 Kg of Heroin Seized in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The police in Guangdong
Province have announced here that they have seized 166 kg of
heroin smuggled by three drug-trafficking gangs.
</P>
<P>
The haul was confiscated in Jieyang City. Most of it was found
hidden in the driver's seat of a truck, and is thought to have
originated in Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
It was the biggest drug smuggling case cracked in the province
this year. Police have arrested 11 suspects, who reportedly were
members of three gangs based in Guangdong and Yunnan provinces in
southern China.
</P>
<P>
Several of their accomplices are still at large, according to
the Jieyang police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
