<HEADLINE> Grenade Kills Two in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A grenade explosion killed two
people and injured 28 others in the southern Philippines on
Sunday, a report of the SNN TV station said.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the grenade exploded during a clash
between residents and government workers demolishing illegally
built shanties in Tacurong town in Sultan Kudarat province, about
1,000 kilometers south of Manila.
</P>
<P>
Those who died were residents of the shanties and several
policemen were injured in the accident, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Government workers, backed by police, were demolishing dozens
of slums when the grenade blasted near a group of residents who
were protesting the action of the government.
</P>
<P>
The local police are investigating the incident but no people
have been arrested, the report said. 
</P>
