<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 15 (Xinhua) -- More than 8,000 South Korean
policemen surrounded the Seoul National University on Sunday to
block thousands of students from marching to the border truce
village Pammunjom to attend a rally on unification.
</P>
<P>
Over 4,000 students, who had planned to hold the rally with
compatriots from the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
and overseas Koreans on the day marking the 54th anniversary of
Korea's liberation from Japanese colonial rule, encountered the
blockade as they were leaving the campus for Pammunjom.
</P>
