<HEADLINE> Shandong Beat Dalian in Chinese Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Shandong beat Dalian Wanda 1-0
in the 19th round of the Chinese First Division Soccer League,
clinching their first-ever victory over the four-time champions
since the league was inaugurated in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Shandong scored the lone goal at the 26th minute as unmarked
striker Su Maozhen tapped the ball home, sending Dalian to the
10th place in the standings.
</P>
<P>
Dalian didn't show their former touch and flair this season
after their top striker Hao Haidong was banned for six months by
the Asian Football Federation for his spitting at a referee in the
Asian Games last December.
</P>
<P>
Dalian have only won four games this season with a poor 20
points.
</P>
<P>
Shandong kept their second place with 36 points, just one point
away from the league leader Liaoning, which downed Guangzhou 1-0
on a second-half goal by Zhang Yuning.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan nipped Tianjin 3-2 to secure full three points and the
third place, while Shanghai Shenhua saw their 2-0 lead over
Beijing reduced to 2-2 at the final whistle.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai was fourth with 30 points.
</P>
<P>
Jilin romped over Chongqing 3-1, avenging a 2-6 away loss in
their first encounter, while Wuhan edged out Shenyang 1-0, and
Shenzhen downed Qingdao 2-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
