military operations against the PKK in the southeast although
imprisoned PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan called his fellowers to
stop armed struggle and withdraw from the Turkish territory from
September 1.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been waging a separatist campaign for an
independent Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey since 1984, which
has claimed over 37,000 lives in. 
