<DOCNO> XIE19990815.0076 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Win World Women's Volleyball GP in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Brazil overcame
early setbacks to beat local favorites China 3-1, winning the
Macao leg of World Women's Volleyball Grand Prix here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The scores were 20-25, 25-22, 31-29, 25-16.
</P>
<P>
"We played too timidly in the first set, then we changed our
tactics and played aggressively, " said delighted Brazilian head
coach Bernardo Rocha de Rezende.
</P>
<P>
Asked why China performed so differently compared with their
brilliant show in Switzerland and Australia, Chinese head coach Hu
Jin said: "We played better there only because our rivals didn't
play well. "
</P>
<P>
Italy beat the Netherlands 25-20, 26-24, 22-25, 25-21 on Sunday,
placing second in the event with two wins and one loss. China
finished third with one win against two losses, followed by the
Netherlands which lost three games.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese, world and Olympic runners-up, jumped to a flying
start by producing a flurry of fierce attacks and tight blocks
that caught the Brazilians out of position, winning the first set
25-20.
</P>
<P>
But the second set saw the Brazilians, who had been beaten by
the Chinese twice recently, turning the tables 25-22 mainly on the
10 unforced mistakes by the Chinese.
</P>
<P>
The highlight of the match occurred in the third set when the
two teams leveled 10 times from 20-all to 29-all. After saving
four set points, Brazil finished the tough set 31-29 with a
powerful spike and a block-out from their opponent.
</P>
<P>
Brazil played some of their best volleyball that kept their
arch-rivals scrambling with superb offense and defense in the
fourth set, leading all the way to seal the match with an easy
score of 25-16.
</P>
<P>
Veteran Virna Kias of Brazil was crowned most valuable player
and best server of the Macao leg. The most welcomed player went to
Chinese setter Zhu Yunying.
</P>
<P>
The world top eight women's teams will be re-grouped and
compete at Chinese Taipei and the Philippines legs in next weekend.
Then China, as host, and the top three teams at the four legs of
the Grand Prix will go to southwest China's Yunnan province to
decide the winner of the GP finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
