<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Consumer Confidence Boosted in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 15 (Xinhua) -- General consumer confidence
improved in Kuwait in July after the formation of the new
government, which comprises a strong economic team, an opinion
poll published here Sunday showed.
</P>
<P>
The poll, conducted by Ipsos Stat, a local marketing research
company, and obtained by the Arab Times newspaper, showed that the
consumer confidence index picked up by four points to 67 in July,
the third best result in the past 12 months.
</P>
<P>
The poll is conducted monthly among 1,000 randomly selected
men and is aimed at reflecting people's opinion on Kuwait's
current and future economic situation, the security situation,
expectations about future purchasing power and the level of
satisfaction with personal income. All index figures show the
ratio on a zero-to-100-point scale.
</P>
<P>
Ipsos Stat said the increase came as a surprise as it had
expected consumer confidence to drop during the month when
Kuwaitis and expatriates were abroad spending their summer
vacations.
</P>
<P>
Instead, it said "the parliament elections and the subsequent
formation of a new government with a strong economic component
were welcomed by local consumers, who were given impetus to spend
more on local goods."
</P>
<P>
According to the poll, although people's perception of the
current economic situation remained weak, with the indicator
rising to 40 from 37, their perception of the future economic
performance was very positive, with the index climbing to 74
points.
</P>
<P>
Satisfaction with personal income also improved during the
month of July, with 66 percent, a 6 percent rise.
</P>
<P>
Both Kuwaitis and expatriates were expecting an improvement in
people's purchasing power in the future as the index picked up by
6 points to 70.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti and expatriate consumers were feeling more secure in
the Gulf state, with security situation index gained 8 points
to 81 in July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
