China's Shanxi Province, have arrested four people on charges of
being involved in trafficking in cultural relics.
</P>
<P>
Police seized eight cultural items which date back to the Han (
206 B.C and 24) and Ming (1368-1644) dynasties -- two porcelain
pots, two teacups, a pair of bronze water pipes and two stone
Buddhas.
