<HEADLINE> Inflation Rises By 0.4 Percent in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 15 (Xinhua) -- India's inflation rate went up
0.4 percent to 1.62 percent for the week that ended on July 31,
mainly due to rises in prices of food and fuel.
</P>
<P>
According to the Reserve Bank of India, India's annual
inflation rate based on Wholesale Price Index recorded a
two-decade low of 1.19 percent last week.
</P>
<P>
The lower rate of inflation this year is mainly on account of a
higher base last year when prices of food articles, especially
vegetables rose substantially. 
</P>
</TEXT>
