<HEADLINE> Castro to Seek 2008 Olympic Games for Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Cuban President Fidel Castro said
on Saturday that his country will vie for the 2008 or the 2012
Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Castro spent his 73rd birthday with the Cuban athletes that
took part in the recent 13th Pan-American Games in Winnipeg,
Canada, where they obtained second place after the United States.
