<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Celebrations of 85th Anniversary of Panama Canal Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The events to commemorate
the 85th anniversary of the Panama Canal started here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rican President Miguel Angel Rodriguez, his Colombian
counterpart Andres Pastrana, as well as General Secretary of the
Organization of American States (OAS) Cesar Gaviria, will attend
the celebrations.
</P>
<P>
Mexican Foreign Minister and a Venezuelan senator will
represent their presidents to attend the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The guests will take a tour to the zone of the canal and attend
an official ceremony Sunday night at the National Theater in which
the "Declaration of Panama" is to be signed.
</P>
<P>
The canal will revert to Panamanian sovereignty on December 31
this year under the 1977 Torrijos-Carter Treaties.  
</P>
</TEXT>
