<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Qi Strikes Double Golds in Pool </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 18 (Xinhua) -- China's Qi Hui struck double
golds in swimming here on Saturday at the Military World Games
when she triumphed in women's 50 meters breaststroke and 200
meters medley.
</P>
<P>
Qi won the 50 meters in 32.20 seconds, beating Ukraine's
European championships runner-up Svitlana Bondarenko to the second
place. Slovenia's Natasa Kejzar took the third place.
</P>
<P>
Qi, Asian Games runner-up in 200 meters breaststroke, said
Saturday's result was her personal best.
</P>
<P>
"I improved by one second over last year," she added. "This
race, like any other 50 meters race, does not leave much room for
errors and every mistake is punished. I made no mistakes and that
makes me very happy."
</P>
<P>
Qi's time in the 200 meters medley was two minutes 17.47
seconds, more than two seconds ahead of Natasa Kejzar and Alenka
Kejzar, both Slovenian, in second and third places.
</P>
<P>
Slovenia's Metka Sparavec achieved same feat by winning two
golds to bring her gold collection to three here.
</P>
<P>
She finished the 50 meters freestyle in 26.14 seconds, beating
China's Le Ying to second in 26.16.
</P>
<P>
Sparavec, who also took the 50 meters backstroke title in 29.46,
said: "When it started, it was plain sailing. This is my third
gold in Zagreb and I sincerely haven't expected such an
achievement."
</P>
<P>
In the day's other actions, European chamionships silver
medalist Gordan Kozulj took an easy cruise in men's 100 meters
backstroke to win the gold in 56.26 while the Russians were first
in men's 4x100 meters freestyle relay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
