<HEADLINE> Sampras Beats Agassi to Reach ATP Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- World No. 1 Pete Sampras of
the United States beat his countryman Andre Agassi in the
semifinals of the ATP Championship here today in California.
</P>
<P>
Sampras got his third chance in five weeks to defeat Agassi 7-6
(9-7), 6-4. He survived a tough tie-breaker and controlled the
opening of the second set.
</P>
<P>
Agassi hit the tape with an open passing shot to give Sampras
an 8-7 lead in the tie-break, and Sampras won the next point and
the first four games of the second set.
</P>
<P>
Patrick Rafter or Yevgeny Kafelnikov will try to end Sampras'
21-match winning streak in the finals tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Today marks the first time in six years the top four seeds of
an event all reached the semifinals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
