<HEADLINE> Mexican Navy Seizes 10 Tons of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Navy Saturday
seized 10 tons of cocaine in a fishing boat off the coast of the
states of Michoacan and Guerrero, in the south of the country.
</P>
<P>
The drug was discovered during the Navy's routine inspection of
the Mexican ship "Xoloescuintle" in the Pacific Ocean, 473
kilometers away from the Lazaro Cardenas port in Michoacan, said a
Navy Ministry statement.
</P>
<P>
The drug was contained in packages hidden in the hold of the
fishing ship.
</P>
<P>
The Navy did not say whether the 16-man crew of the ship were
detained.
</P>
<P>
Three cannon-equipped ships and a destroyer took part in the
operation. 
</P>
