<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man United Climbe to Top of Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Two goals from Dwight Yorke took
Manchester United to a 2-0 home victory over Leeds United at the
English Premier League on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
With the win, the treble winner club of last season climbed to
the top of the league.
</P>
<P>
While on the soil of Anfield at West England, newly promoted
Watford won 1-0 at big-spending Liverpool.
</P>
<P>
Yorke struck with headers in the 76th and 80th minutes to
settle the game but United's celebrations were slightly muted by
the news that captain Roy Keane has refused to sign a new contract
and will consider his future at the end of the season.
</P>
<P>
Watford, hot favourites for relegation, had never so much as
drawn at Anfield but took all three points with a 14th minute goal
by Tommy Mooney.
</P>
<P>
Leicester's Frank Sinclair scored a last minute own goal for
the second successive week to give Chelsea a 2-2 draw just a
minute after a Muzzy Izzet's penalty had put Leicester ahead.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal were unable to break through Sunderland's defence at
the Stadium of Light and had to settle for a goalless draw while
Tottenham Hotspur twice came from behind to beat Everton 3-2.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
