<HEADLINE> Six Pakistanis Killed as Bomb Explodes in Passenger Van </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 15 (Xinhua) -- At least six people were
killed and 14 others injured Saturday when a powerful bomb went
off in a passenger van in northern Pakistan, reported the
Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place at about 13:30 p.m. in a Ford van which
was passing by Dina, a small town about 70 kilometers southeast of
Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
According to police, the van was blasted with a high explosive
plastic device weighing 5 kilograms. 
