<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sixers Acquire Owens from Magic for Grant, Parker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Philadelphia 76ers
acquired much-traveled forward Billy Owens from the Orlando Magic,
who continue to wheel and deal.
</P>
<P>
The 76ers signed free agent forward Harvey Grant and packaged
him with little-used guard Anthony Parker to land Owens, who has
been traded twice in just over a month. On June 30, he was dealt
from the Seattle SuperSonics to Orlando in a five-player swap.
</P>
<P>
In an injury-plagued campaign, Owens averaged career lows of 7.
8 points and 3.8 rebounds in 21 games for the SuperSonics last
season. He was sidelined early in the campaign by a broken hand.
</P>
<P>
Owens has averaged 13 points and seven rebounds per game in his
eight-year career. He joins his seventh team and always has
displayed uncommon skills for a big player.
</P>
<P>
The Magic continue to stockpile players in the final year of
their contracts. They have traded four starters from last season's
playoff squad and have 14 players under contract, most of whom
become free agents after the 1999-2000 season.
</P>
<P>
Grant aeraged 3.1 points and 2.3 rebounds in 47 games last
season. He is the twin brother of forward Horace Grant, who spent
five seasons with the Magic before being dealt to Seattle.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, the 76ers re-signed free agent guard Eric
Snow and forward George Lynch to multi-year contracts. They return
the nucleus of a team that made the playoffs for the first time in
eight years and upset Orlando in the first round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
