<HEADLINE> Fidel Castro to Seek 2008 Olympic Games For Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Cuban President Fidel Castro said
on Saturday that his counry will bid to host the 2008 or the 2012
Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Castro spent his 73rd birthday with the Cuban athletes that
took part in the recent 13th Panamerican Games in Winnipeg, Canada,
where they obtained second place after the United States in the
medals table.
</P>
<P>
The president gave a Cuban flag to the team that will take part
in the Boxing World Championship to be held August 20 in Houston,
United States.
</P>
<P>
"The battle starts now, although it does not mean that justice
will be done in 2008, but will in the 2012, and I do not think it
will go beyond 2016 if we fight appropriately," said Castro in his
speech.
</P>
<P>
Fidel Castro explained that the Cuban sports authorities have
not started yet the formal procedures for the bid of the 2008
Olympic Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
