<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five Patients Found in Albania Due to Eclipse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Five people have been found with
eye problems in Albania after observing the solar eclipse, the
Albanian Telegraphic Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The patients, aged 18-25, are residents in Albania's southern
city of Elbasan. Doctors said that they watched the eclipse
without defensive means.
</P>
<P>
One of the patients has serious problems with the eye retina
and is likely to lose sight.
</P>
<P>
The results of the other four, who were receiving medical
treatment at local clinics, are unknown.
</P>
<P>
A partial solar eclipse was seen in Albania last Wednesday.
Many Albanians, frightened by the phenomenon, confined themselves
to the house to watch it, or chose to watch through television due
to lack of defensive means, like sun glasses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
