<DOCNO> XIE19990815.0173 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afro-China Council Supports One-China Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Council for Afro-China
Affairs, a Nigeria-based African non-governmental organization
expressed here Saturday its full support of one-China policy.
</P>
<P>
"The council fully supports the just struggle of the Chinese
people to re-unite their motherland under the internationally
recognized government in Beijing", said chairman of the
organization Essien at a party in the Abuja Office of the Chinese
Embassy.
</P>
<P>
"We therefore urge the Taiwan authorities to respond positively
to the constructive proposal of the central government for a
peaceful re-unification of China, and restrain from utterances and
activities that undermine the unification," he said.
</P>
<P>
Africa, which suffered from the arbitrarily carving out by
foreign powers, knows very well the scars of such partitioning as
left-over from history, he added.
</P>
<P>
It is the council's view that China will never have a "state to
state" relation with Taiwan, whether it is special or not, and
therefore, it urged the Taiwan authorities to face squarely the
historically-determined route of national reunification, he said.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
